I don't hate it. You did put a lot of thought into this, but it feels like you have to go through too much to get too little in return. There's no real twist, apart from the Cleric becoming cooperative due to increased wisdom, which is actually my least favorite part of the entire piece because it labels the Foundation's activities as  rather than ambiguous. Bard's charisma feels like a cop out because he has a magical smile instead of being better at understanding and manipulating people.

A better twist would have been the super intelligent warlock using his new stats to screw everyone else and escape not by getting out of the Foundation but tricking everyone into believing that he is actually one of the head researchers who was working within the game and falsifying necessary records to support that.







